1
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:34,320
=Hold a Court Now=

2
00:01:35,260 --> 00:01:38,500
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:39,100 --> 00:01:41,140
But the judge
was actually pretty effective.

4
00:01:41,270 --> 00:01:44,540
Looks like Li Zhoucheng
might end up with almost nothing.

5
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,030
Sis,

6
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:55,540
I know

7
00:01:55,820 --> 00:01:59,140
this has hit you pretty hard.

8
00:01:59,790 --> 00:02:02,670
Life can be pretty rough sometimes.

9
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:04,659
But I think

10
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:06,379
for a woman like you,

11
00:02:06,380 --> 00:02:07,869
this case might not
necessarily be a bad thing.

12
00:02:07,870 --> 00:02:09,710
And with your qualities,

13
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:11,470
just take a little time,

14
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:13,299
freshen yourself up a bit,

15
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:15,299
hit the gym
and get a trainer to shape up.

16
00:02:15,300 --> 00:02:16,299
You might just find

17
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,940
a second chance at love soon.

18
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,310
I don't want any second chance.

19
00:02:23,550 --> 00:02:25,780
I just want my husband.

20
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:27,709
Sis...

21
00:02:27,710 --> 00:02:29,059
This is all your fault.

22
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:32,389
Didn't you say the judge wouldn't rule?

23
00:02:32,390 --> 00:02:36,060
If the judge really grants the divorce,
what am I supposed to do?

24
00:02:36,110 --> 00:02:39,389
What kind of advice did you give me?

25
00:02:39,390 --> 00:02:41,269
But when the judge asked
for your opinion just now,

26
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:43,149
weren't you pretty firm about it?

27
00:02:43,150 --> 00:02:44,660
I don't care.

28
00:02:45,020 --> 00:02:46,579
You have to fix this for me.

29
00:02:46,580 --> 00:02:48,150
I'm not getting divorced.

30
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:50,899
How about this?

31
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:51,949
No divorce.

32
00:02:51,950 --> 00:02:52,829
We won't divorce.

33
00:02:52,830 --> 00:02:55,660
When you get home, just tell your husband
we're not divorcing anymore.

34
00:02:56,180 --> 00:02:57,550
Why should I?

35
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,150
You go tell him.

36
00:03:00,230 --> 00:03:01,459
You're the one who messed this up.

37
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:03,220
You go make him sort this out for me.

38
00:03:03,230 --> 00:03:04,430
Fine.

39
00:03:04,780 --> 00:03:05,949
I'll talk to the judge.

40
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:07,549
As long as you say you regret it,

41
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:09,680
you're the plaintiff,
the judge will definitely side with you.

42
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,500
No.

43
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:11,709
If he finds out this time

44
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:13,389
it's me going back on my word again,

45
00:03:13,390 --> 00:03:16,380
I'll be in an even
worse position with him.

46
00:03:16,710 --> 00:03:17,829
Let me tell you,

47
00:03:17,830 --> 00:03:19,019
you made this mess,

48
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:21,149
you fix it.

49
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:23,220
If you can't fix this,

50
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:25,660
you'll compensate me tenfold.

51
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:29,060
Sis.

52
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:44,059
(Jindian Law Firm)

53
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:46,299
Is this the collapse of human nature,

54
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:47,949
or the decay of morality?

55
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:50,579
Let's take a look together
at Rui's Legal Lens.

56
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:51,299
No more introductions,

57
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,150
today we're focusing on

58
00:03:53,830 --> 00:03:55,779
a case that's gone viral online.

59
00:03:55,780 --> 00:03:59,100
A vicious daughter-in-law versus
a "virus-like" mother-in-law.

60
00:03:59,180 --> 00:04:01,149
A virus passed on to a child

61
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,549
was it an accident,

62
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:04,750
or done on purpose?

63
00:04:04,950 --> 00:04:08,070
(Liu Wenbo)

64
00:04:09,720 --> 00:04:11,619
Hello? Mr. Liu.

65
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,550
Why haven't you
been answering your phone?

66
00:04:13,870 --> 00:04:15,869
I was recording content
for my public account.

67
00:04:15,870 --> 00:04:16,699
At a time like this,

68
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:17,909
I'm practically panicking,

69
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:19,499
and you're still messing
with that useless stuff.

70
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,790
Let me tell you,

71
00:04:20,820 --> 00:04:22,379
I went to three hospitals
this afternoon,

72
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:24,260
not a single one
would issue that certificate.

73
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,550
Right,

74
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:30,669
most reputable hospitals are indeed unwilling
to provide that kind of certification.

75
00:04:30,670 --> 00:04:32,910
I went to less formal ones too,
they still wouldn't issue it.

76
00:04:34,590 --> 00:04:35,549
Then,

77
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:38,549
when you said that in court earlier,

78
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,430
had you already thought it through?

79
00:04:40,590 --> 00:04:42,430
You really don't plan
on having children anymore?

80
00:04:42,740 --> 00:04:44,060
What are you implying?

81
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,260
Mr. Liu,

82
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,430
have you considered

83
00:04:50,550 --> 00:04:54,670
actually undergoing
a sterilization procedure?

84
00:04:56,990 --> 00:04:59,110
Do you hear yourself?

85
00:04:59,260 --> 00:05:00,670
Qin Rui,

86
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:03,619
back in court, I said that because you
had no other options,

87
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:05,589
I was trying to help you
think of a way out.

88
00:05:05,590 --> 00:05:06,429
Why do you keep giving me

89
00:05:06,430 --> 00:05:08,429
these ridiculous ideas?

90
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:09,869
Let me tell you,

91
00:05:09,870 --> 00:05:11,179
I chose your firm

92
00:05:11,180 --> 00:05:12,259
because I meant well,

93
00:05:12,260 --> 00:05:13,469
I was supporting your business.

94
00:05:13,470 --> 00:05:14,349
Other than being cheap,

95
00:05:14,350 --> 00:05:15,909
you haven't solved
a single problem for me.

96
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:17,989
And today I even checked
with a major law firm.

97
00:05:17,990 --> 00:05:19,179
Even their interns

98
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,429
have great energy

99
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:22,380
and professionalism.

100
00:05:22,550 --> 00:05:23,429
Their director

101
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,739
is a winning expert,
a top figure in the field.

102
00:05:25,740 --> 00:05:28,229
They have plenty
of strategies and solutions.

103
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:29,589
Do you even realize

104
00:05:29,590 --> 00:05:31,499
cases like this are easy for them?

105
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,550
The child will definitely
be awarded to me.

106
00:05:33,790 --> 00:05:36,179
Do you really think
what they said is reliable?

107
00:05:36,180 --> 00:05:37,699
When they're trying to take on a case...

108
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,700
How could it not be true?

109
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:41,109
Let me tell you,

110
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:42,179
someone at your level

111
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:44,109
doesn't understand
what real professionalism is.

112
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:45,589
Look at the level they operate at.

113
00:05:45,590 --> 00:05:47,600
Their resources are
on a completely different starting line.

114
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,349
And they also said

115
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:50,699
a case like mine can be handled
on a contingency basis,

116
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:53,059
work first, payment later,

117
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:54,989
only pay if we win the case.

118
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:57,909
Do you understand? That's what
real professional service is.

119
00:05:57,910 --> 00:05:59,580
What kind of lousy firm are you running?

120
00:05:59,870 --> 00:06:02,060
If you can't handle this,
I'll find someone else.

121
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:04,549
Mr. Liu,

122
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:05,499
how about this?

123
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:07,060
Give me a bit more time.

124
00:06:07,140 --> 00:06:08,989
I'll definitely try
to figure something out for you.

125
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:10,259
I'll give you three days.

126
00:06:10,260 --> 00:06:12,059
Otherwise, either you
get me that fake certificate,

127
00:06:12,060 --> 00:06:14,179
or I'll find someone else.

128
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:15,350
That's it.

129
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:24,989
(Forensic Identification Center)

130
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:27,060
Lian, do you know what he said to me?

131
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,429
With that kind of attitude,

132
00:06:28,430 --> 00:06:30,029
then he should just go to them.

133
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:30,869
Stingy as can be.

134
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:32,990
I've been running around
for him this whole time,

135
00:06:33,180 --> 00:06:35,140
and he only gave me a 300 deposit.

136
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:38,020
And he still brings up
those big law firms.

137
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:39,589
So they're the professionals,

138
00:06:39,590 --> 00:06:41,379
and I'm the one using shady tricks?

139
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:43,029
That's just talk.

140
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:45,020
Winning a case
isn't about boasting, okay?

141
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:47,820
Do you know what people like that are?

142
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:50,870
Like country folks in a mall

143
00:06:50,940 --> 00:06:53,460
completely lost,
only recognizing big brands.

144
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:55,429
Is it even worth arguing with them?

145
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:56,620
Honestly.

146
00:06:56,870 --> 00:06:58,580
Do you think I'm

147
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:01,430
not as capable as I thought I was?

148
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,940
Give me a break.

149
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:06,299
Don't put yourself down.

150
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,469
Let me tell you,

151
00:07:07,470 --> 00:07:08,699
I just

152
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,380
don't like people like that.

153
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:12,179
Look around now,

154
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,870
who still worships elites like that?

155
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,589
Everyone's pretty clear-headed.

156
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:16,909
What people actually like

157
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:18,429
is someone approachable like you.

158
00:07:18,430 --> 00:07:19,670
Do you get it?

159
00:07:20,110 --> 00:07:21,870
I know you're trying to comfort me.

160
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:24,140
Thank you.

161
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,819
Who's comforting you?

162
00:07:25,820 --> 00:07:27,500
I'm stating facts.

163
00:07:28,670 --> 00:07:30,500
Before I met you,

164
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,260
I never thought

165
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:33,739
someone could have

166
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:36,059
so many interesting ideas in their head.

167
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:38,140
All kinds of unusual approaches.

168
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:41,990
They might be a bit all over the place,

169
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:44,380
but that's your core strength.

170
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:47,499
Exactly. So what if it's unconventional?

171
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,619
Who says a small firm like ours

172
00:07:48,620 --> 00:07:50,429
can't produce a top-tier lawyer?

173
00:07:50,430 --> 00:07:51,259
Does every lawyer

174
00:07:51,260 --> 00:07:53,550
have to squeeze into those elite firms?

175
00:07:54,110 --> 00:07:55,430
Exactly.

176
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:58,739
How about this, Lian,

177
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,379
I really need you
to help me out this time.

178
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:02,460
Get me a certificate
proving male infertility.

179
00:08:02,990 --> 00:08:03,990
Male...

180
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,259
(Dissection Room)
Are you serious?

181
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,790
Will one from a dead person work?

182
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:11,550
You really have no sense of humor.

183
00:08:11,670 --> 00:08:14,349
Then... I'll figure something out myself.

184
00:08:14,350 --> 00:08:15,580
I'm hanging up now.

185
00:08:18,940 --> 00:08:20,700
What are you in such a hurry for?

186
00:08:23,990 --> 00:08:26,060
Let me go find some inspiration.

187
00:08:26,470 --> 00:08:27,840
(This sense of responsibility and commitment
not only includes financial support,)

188
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:28,429
(but also caring for and raising the child.)

189
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:29,820
All rise.

190
00:08:32,380 --> 00:08:33,589
(Deputy Chief Judge, Shu Jing.)

191
00:08:33,590 --> 00:08:34,710
(Presiding Judge)

192
00:08:35,830 --> 00:08:38,949
(Has a child, empathetic, fair.)

193
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:41,150
When I married the defendant,
I was still young.

194
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:43,139
She went out to clubs

195
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:44,429
and stayed out all night.

196
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:48,309
(Serious, fair, empathetic)

197
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:49,419
(In her eyes,)

198
00:08:49,420 --> 00:08:52,060
(Sun Lala is definitely
not a qualified mother.)

199
00:08:53,590 --> 00:08:55,150
(Judge Yu)

200
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:57,019
(Young and promising.)

201
00:08:57,020 --> 00:08:58,790
(Fair-skinned, attractive.)

202
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:00,310
(Happily married.)

203
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:04,349
(She believes
Sun Lala's family environment)

204
00:09:04,350 --> 00:09:06,190
(will affect Xiaolongbao's upbringing.)

205
00:09:07,350 --> 00:09:09,109
What is the situation
with the defendant's parents?

206
00:09:09,110 --> 00:09:11,019
The defendant's parents divorced,
then each remarried,

207
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:12,539
and then both divorced again.

208
00:09:12,540 --> 00:09:14,589
A nanny earning eight thousand a month,

209
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:16,069
there are plenty to choose from.

210
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:16,829
She might not even know

211
00:09:16,830 --> 00:09:18,429
whether her parents are still alive.

212
00:09:18,430 --> 00:09:20,750
(Decisive, sharp,
clear about right and wrong)

213
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:23,030
(Shen Xiezhi)

214
00:09:24,140 --> 00:09:25,790
(Cold and detached.)

215
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:28,069
(He is like a machine
that hands down judgments.)

216
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:28,910
(Panel Judge)

217
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:30,779
(I never expected much from him anyway.)

218
00:09:30,780 --> 00:09:32,350
(Arrogant, indifferent,
hard to approach)

219
00:09:36,590 --> 00:09:39,670
(The two female judges
still had some hope at first,)

220
00:09:39,710 --> 00:09:41,510
(but after Liu Wenbo caused a scene,)

221
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,310
(those two votes are now uncertain.)

222
00:09:46,660 --> 00:09:48,139
(Now it seems)

223
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:50,060
(every vote has to be secured.)

224
00:09:51,990 --> 00:09:55,060
Heaven, give me some inspiration.

225
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:06,390
Listen to yourself.

226
00:10:06,740 --> 00:10:08,390
We've known each other for years.

227
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:10,259
I may not be able
to help you with everything,

228
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:12,150
but when it comes to deciding
a case, that's my specialty.

229
00:10:12,350 --> 00:10:14,069
That depends on what you want.

230
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:15,019
If you want something,

231
00:10:15,020 --> 00:10:16,740
you've got to give something in return.

232
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:18,349
Then hurry up,

233
00:10:18,350 --> 00:10:19,160
get over here.

234
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,760
Bring something nice
and make it worth my while.

235
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:21,739
When the time comes,

236
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:23,390
I'll put in a good word for you.

237
00:10:23,660 --> 00:10:24,259
Come on, move it.

238
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,390
(Bribe?)

239
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,259
(So this is who you are, Shen Xiezhi.)

240
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,899
(I thought that Liu Wenbo was bluffing.)

241
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,790
(You always talking
about morality and legal principles,)

242
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:35,790
(and yet doing something
so dirty behind the scenes.)

243
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:40,060
What did you bring?

244
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,910
Keeping it a secret?

245
00:10:59,420 --> 00:11:00,790
Looking for me?

246
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:07,069
As a lawyer,

247
00:11:07,070 --> 00:11:09,739
following the presiding judge
of your case in the middle of the night,

248
00:11:09,740 --> 00:11:11,060
what exactly are you trying to do?

249
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,820
Say something.

250
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:16,229
I...

251
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:17,419
What do you mean "I"?

252
00:11:17,420 --> 00:11:18,779
If you can't give
a reasonable explanation,

253
00:11:18,780 --> 00:11:20,150
I'm calling the police.

254
00:11:20,190 --> 00:11:21,469
Don't try to twist this around.

255
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:23,189
Twist it around?

256
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:24,989
What kind of shady business
are you up to here?

257
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:26,259
You think I don't know?

258
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:27,860
I recorded everything.

259
00:11:28,660 --> 00:11:30,949
What shady business?
What exactly did you record?

260
00:11:30,950 --> 00:11:32,139
Evidence.

261
00:11:32,140 --> 00:11:33,829
You taking bribes and giving them.

262
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:35,220
That's all evidence.

263
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:37,940
Me, taking bribes?

264
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:41,589
You follow a judge
in the middle of the night,

265
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:42,989
and then make false accusations.

266
00:11:42,990 --> 00:11:44,340
I'm calling the police right now.

267
00:11:45,660 --> 00:11:47,589
Why are you calling the police?
Just talk this out.

268
00:11:47,590 --> 00:11:48,379
Don't touch me, let go.

269
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:49,899
- Don't call the police, what are you doing?
- Don't touch me.

270
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:51,109
- Don't call the police.
- Let go, give it to me.

271
00:11:51,110 --> 00:11:51,539
Now you're the one

272
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:52,630
- making false accusations?
- What's going on here?

273
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,100
This...

274
00:11:56,830 --> 00:11:58,019
Judge Jiang,

275
00:11:58,020 --> 00:11:59,630
you came at the right time.

276
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:01,229
Perfect, you can be a witness.

277
00:12:01,230 --> 00:12:02,709
Just now, in the dark,

278
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:03,829
he was taking and giving bribes,

279
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:05,980
and now he's trying
to flip it and call the police.

280
00:12:06,540 --> 00:12:07,790
What exactly is going on?

281
00:12:08,780 --> 00:12:10,790
You sure picked your moment.

282
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:12,379
Ms. Qin,

283
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:14,349
let me introduce you.

284
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:16,539
This is the one bribing me.

285
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:18,310
Jiang Feng, Judge Jiang.

286
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:19,309
The two of us

287
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:21,309
made plans to go home together
and break the law.

288
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:23,220
My place is right behind us.

289
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:26,940
Right, I'm the one doing the bribing.

290
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:28,619
Lawyers are always chasing after us,

291
00:12:28,620 --> 00:12:29,619
trying to influence us.

292
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:32,150
So I brought a bottle
of good wine as a bribe,

293
00:12:32,540 --> 00:12:34,510
and just asked him
to help me think of a solution.

294
00:12:36,110 --> 00:12:37,619
This wine really isn't bad.

295
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:39,150
Must be worth about two hundred, right?

296
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:42,940
Two hundred? How many years
does that get him for bribery?

297
00:12:44,380 --> 00:12:46,019
Maybe we should just call the police.

298
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:46,989
No.

299
00:12:46,990 --> 00:12:49,270
Why are you always
jumping to call the police?

300
00:12:50,140 --> 00:12:51,790
What a coincidence.

301
00:12:56,590 --> 00:12:57,829
How did I not think of this?

302
00:12:57,830 --> 00:12:59,189
So you two are actually friends.

303
00:12:59,190 --> 00:13:00,899
With wine like this,
you need a couple of dishes.

304
00:13:00,900 --> 00:13:01,949
And something filling too,

305
00:13:01,950 --> 00:13:03,379
otherwise it's easy to get drunk.

306
00:13:03,380 --> 00:13:04,109
Judge Shen,

307
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,829
drink a little less. Stay in touch.

308
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:07,709
Stay in touch, give me a call.

309
00:13:07,710 --> 00:13:09,150
WeChat works too.

310
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:13,220
What's wrong with her?

311
00:13:14,070 --> 00:13:15,510
She's already drunk.

312
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:30,100
Finally made a hundred million, huh?

313
00:13:34,470 --> 00:13:35,580
I'm done for.

314
00:13:36,870 --> 00:13:38,940
I just finished my last bite of noodles.

315
00:13:40,110 --> 00:13:41,670
Want some soup?

316
00:13:49,070 --> 00:13:50,189
I'm starving.

317
00:13:50,190 --> 00:13:50,949
Been busy all night,

318
00:13:50,950 --> 00:13:52,630
didn't even get a chance to eat.

319
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:55,019
I originally planned to catch
that judge taking bribes,

320
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:57,060
who knew the one offering
the bribe would be Jiang Feng.

321
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,060
I've completely embarrassed myself.

322
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:04,069
This time I've probably
offended the judge too.

323
00:14:04,070 --> 00:14:05,340
Stop thinking about it.

324
00:14:05,380 --> 00:14:07,469
Your grandma sent a package,
it's in the back. Go take a look.

325
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:09,190
Grandma sent another parcel?

326
00:14:13,230 --> 00:14:15,430
What is it? Feels pretty heavy.

327
00:14:21,310 --> 00:14:22,860
More dried goods.

328
00:14:25,590 --> 00:14:27,270
So many things.

329
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:35,619
Same as always,

330
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:37,109
two portions of everything.

331
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:38,510
Half for you, half for me.

332
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:41,109
That's great.

333
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:43,630
Grandma always thinks of me.

334
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:46,109
With this much stuff,

335
00:14:46,110 --> 00:14:47,910
she must've been busy all day again.

336
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:54,190
You can tell just from the smell,
it's that sun-dried scent from grandma.

337
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:01,150
Let's video call her.

338
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:05,950
(Grandma, waiting for answer)

339
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:09,340
Grandma, you picked up so quickly.

340
00:15:09,350 --> 00:15:11,580
We got everything you sent.

341
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:13,139
Hello, Grandma.

342
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:14,899
I received everything.

343
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,310
Lian,

344
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:18,659
you've gotten even prettier.

345
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:19,980
Really?

346
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:21,340
Thank you, Grandma.

347
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,419
Grandma,

348
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:24,139
have you been taking your medicine?

349
00:15:24,140 --> 00:15:25,739
The chickens have been fed.

350
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:28,229
I'm counting on them to lay eggs.

351
00:15:28,230 --> 00:15:30,220
What chickens? I mean your medicine.

352
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:33,060
Medicine?

353
00:15:33,110 --> 00:15:34,659
Medicine, yes, I've taken it.

354
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:36,150
There's still plenty left.

355
00:15:36,190 --> 00:15:37,259
How could there be plenty?

356
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:39,109
(Medicine almost out. Remind Grandma to buy more.)
I've written everything down here.

357
00:15:39,110 --> 00:15:40,259
You've already run out today.

358
00:15:40,260 --> 00:15:41,869
Then how do you still have extra?

359
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:43,460
Have you not been taking it on time?

360
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:45,419
Are you worried I don't have money?

361
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:46,739
Let me tell you, Lian is right here,

362
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:47,829
she can vouch for me.

363
00:15:47,830 --> 00:15:50,419
I'm now the top lawyer at our firm.

364
00:15:50,420 --> 00:15:52,220
I just took on a big case,

365
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:53,989
and I'm even wondering

366
00:15:53,990 --> 00:15:55,580
how to spend all the money I'll make.

367
00:15:57,310 --> 00:16:00,670
My dear, you can earn money now.

368
00:16:01,310 --> 00:16:03,659
I will take my medicine.

369
00:16:03,660 --> 00:16:04,989
Take it properly.

370
00:16:04,990 --> 00:16:06,150
Alright.

371
00:16:06,310 --> 00:16:08,430
Then don't worry about us,
get some rest early.

372
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:09,980
Bye, Grandma.

373
00:16:12,950 --> 00:16:14,980
(Remind Grandma to take her medicine)
She definitely hasn't been taking it on time.

374
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,829
This month,

375
00:16:18,830 --> 00:16:20,069
no matter what it takes,

376
00:16:20,070 --> 00:16:21,700
I have to bring in some income.

377
00:16:24,140 --> 00:16:25,340
Xiang Hui,

378
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:26,910
the schedule is ready.

379
00:16:27,620 --> 00:16:28,419
Send it out.

380
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,390
Okay.

381
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:32,940
I've put the schedule here.

382
00:16:32,990 --> 00:16:33,910
Alright.

383
00:16:38,710 --> 00:16:40,590
(Civil Ruling)

384
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:42,419
Su Qi,

385
00:16:42,420 --> 00:16:43,259
the duty roster.

386
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:44,270
Got it.

387
00:16:45,030 --> 00:16:47,010
- I've put the filled forms on the desk.
- Okay.

388
00:16:50,990 --> 00:16:56,830
(Qingcheng Court Hearing Schedule)

389
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:02,060
Alright.

390
00:17:02,140 --> 00:17:02,779
Your Honor,

391
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,549
this is all my fault.

392
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:05,740
Plaintiff,

393
00:17:05,940 --> 00:17:07,419
(Family Court)
what are you trying to prove

394
00:17:07,420 --> 00:17:08,780
with this evidence?

395
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:10,740
Let him explain it himself.

396
00:17:11,390 --> 00:17:12,349
Your Honor, it's like this.

397
00:17:12,350 --> 00:17:14,509
A couple of years ago,
I bought a lizard,

398
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:16,459
and then I bought

399
00:17:16,460 --> 00:17:17,979
cockroaches as feed.

400
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,190
Alive ones.

401
00:17:19,790 --> 00:17:21,070
Alive.

402
00:17:21,380 --> 00:17:22,869
Once, I accidentally

403
00:17:22,870 --> 00:17:24,269
knocked the container over.

404
00:17:24,270 --> 00:17:26,219
But afterward,
I tried all sorts of methods,

405
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:27,549
like roach traps,

406
00:17:27,550 --> 00:17:28,459
insecticides,

407
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:29,179
I even hired

408
00:17:29,180 --> 00:17:31,309
a professional pest control team.

409
00:17:31,310 --> 00:17:32,780
The result is,

410
00:17:32,870 --> 00:17:34,869
no matter how carefully we moved,

411
00:17:34,870 --> 00:17:36,699
even after spraying
over a dozen cans of insecticide

412
00:17:36,700 --> 00:17:37,749
and sealing the place for days,

413
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:38,939
nothing worked.

414
00:17:38,940 --> 00:17:41,220
Wherever we went, they followed.

415
00:17:41,420 --> 00:17:43,109
Next, I will present evidence

416
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:44,509
of valuable household items

417
00:17:44,510 --> 00:17:45,899
as well as my personal belongings.

418
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,869
I hope you can compensate me
for them in cash.

419
00:17:47,870 --> 00:17:48,789
Honey,

420
00:17:48,790 --> 00:17:50,619
isn't the reason you want a divorce

421
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:52,309
all because of these cockroaches?

422
00:17:52,310 --> 00:17:53,899
You've already made a list, right?

423
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:54,789
Then let's do this.

424
00:17:54,790 --> 00:17:56,459
We'll replace everything on your list

425
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:59,070
with identical items.

426
00:17:59,220 --> 00:18:01,109
(When lifestyle and preferences clash,)

427
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:02,940
(one side has to give in.)

428
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:05,740
(The husband admits fault
and shows a good attitude.)

429
00:18:06,590 --> 00:18:08,460
(Whether to divorce or reconcile,)

430
00:18:08,510 --> 00:18:09,830
(each side has its reasons.)

431
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:11,590
(Mediation is possible.)

432
00:18:11,870 --> 00:18:13,870
(Happy Pill)

433
00:18:23,550 --> 00:18:24,780
Judge Shen,

434
00:18:25,550 --> 00:18:26,699
do you have a moment?

435
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:29,300
Maybe we can talk privately.

436
00:18:29,510 --> 00:18:30,899
If you have something to say,

437
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,349
say it in court.

438
00:18:32,350 --> 00:18:33,939
About Liu Lihua's case,

439
00:18:33,940 --> 00:18:35,269
is it possible not to grant the divorce?

440
00:18:35,270 --> 00:18:37,549
She has solid evidence
of her husband's infidelity,

441
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,869
and her stance is very firm.

442
00:18:38,870 --> 00:18:40,549
I'm respecting the party's wishes.

443
00:18:40,550 --> 00:18:41,870
Yes,

444
00:18:42,140 --> 00:18:44,269
but circumstances change.

445
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,190
She regretted it
right after the hearing.

446
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:48,179
If she regrets it,

447
00:18:48,180 --> 00:18:49,659
she should come to me herself,

448
00:18:49,660 --> 00:18:52,350
or she can withdraw the case.

449
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:56,700
Exactly, Judge Shen,

450
00:18:57,350 --> 00:18:59,419
but my client cares
a lot about her image.

451
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:01,000
She feels awkward coming herself.

452
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,560
She doesn't want to withdraw the case,
and she doesn't want a divorce either.

453
00:19:03,590 --> 00:19:04,589
Besides,

454
00:19:04,590 --> 00:19:06,269
we usually think divorce cases

455
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:07,870
take three or four hearings,

456
00:19:07,900 --> 00:19:09,869
but with you,
it was resolved immediately.

457
00:19:09,870 --> 00:19:12,240
So you're saying you won't be able to
collect your legal fees after this?

458
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:13,300
Yes...

459
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:16,630
That's not what I meant.

460
00:19:17,030 --> 00:19:20,029
I'm not worried about my fees. I truly
have my client's best interests at heart.

461
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,740
Her best interests?

462
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:24,899
Sending her back
to keep serving that man?

463
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:27,029
Family matters are complicated.

464
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:29,139
They're not something
outsiders can fully understand.

465
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,829
Complicated how?

466
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,630
Why don't you explain it to me?

467
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:37,500
Three children.

468
00:19:38,510 --> 00:19:39,899
For an ordinary family,

469
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,419
raising one child is already exhausting,

470
00:19:41,420 --> 00:19:43,109
let alone three.

471
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:46,309
Think about it, in the future,
when the children get married, and have kids,

472
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,540
how could their father not be there?

473
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:50,899
I'm begging you,

474
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,509
please give me another chance.

475
00:19:52,510 --> 00:19:54,260
What's going on?

476
00:19:56,140 --> 00:19:57,940
Have her come to me herself.

477
00:20:01,830 --> 00:20:02,699
I've take my medicine.

478
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:03,829
There's plenty left.

479
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:05,379
How could there still be extra?

480
00:20:05,380 --> 00:20:07,020
Have you not been taking it on time?

481
00:20:08,350 --> 00:20:09,069
This month,

482
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:10,309
no matter what it takes,

483
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:11,830
I have to bring in some income.

484
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:15,190
So you're not going to help?

485
00:20:16,620 --> 00:20:18,300
Look, what is this?

486
00:20:20,900 --> 00:20:21,940
Pesticide.

487
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:24,069
Miss, don't do anything rash.

488
00:20:24,070 --> 00:20:25,460
This has nothing to do with you.

489
00:20:25,700 --> 00:20:27,459
I found this in her bag.

490
00:20:27,460 --> 00:20:29,190
Are you just going
to stand by and do nothing?

491
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,699
Hello, I don't want these items anymore.

492
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:35,740
Please help me return them, thank you.

493
00:20:36,620 --> 00:20:38,460
(This person just won't listen.)

494
00:20:38,790 --> 00:20:40,870
Hey, don't act impulsively.

495
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:44,870
You can't drink that.

496
00:20:45,180 --> 00:20:46,179
You can't leave.

497
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:48,070
Look at her, she's pitiful.

498
00:20:51,790 --> 00:20:52,980
It's okay.

499
00:20:53,550 --> 00:20:55,700
We'll help you.

500
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:56,940
Auntie, give it to me.

501
00:21:12,150 --> 00:21:13,270
Aunt Wang.

502
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:14,349
You're back.

503
00:21:14,350 --> 00:21:15,670
I'm back.

504
00:21:16,790 --> 00:21:17,630
Sis.

505
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,350
Go play.

506
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:23,150
Careful,

507
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,430
slow down.

508
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:43,940
Why did you bring all this stuff home?

509
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:46,980
Emergency backup.

510
00:21:47,420 --> 00:21:49,029
My colleague treated me.

511
00:21:49,030 --> 00:21:50,300
Nice, right?

512
00:21:51,420 --> 00:21:55,220
New and pretty tools
really lift the mood.

513
00:21:57,830 --> 00:21:58,829
What happened to your arm?

514
00:21:58,830 --> 00:22:00,659
This is my stress-relief exercise.

515
00:22:00,660 --> 00:22:01,830
I'm so mad.

516
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:02,979
Another case fell through.

517
00:22:02,980 --> 00:22:04,309
Got it, I understand.

518
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:06,219
I'll keep supporting you, alright?

519
00:22:06,220 --> 00:22:07,309
There's a sandwich in the fridge.

520
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:08,780
Go eat it.

521
00:22:13,590 --> 00:22:15,109
This time it really wasn't my fault.

522
00:22:15,110 --> 00:22:16,320
It was that judge.

523
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:18,459
Whether I'm capable or not, he should
at least give me a chance to show it.

524
00:22:18,460 --> 00:22:20,069
I hadn't even gotten started,

525
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:22,590
and he just ended the whole thing.

526
00:22:23,270 --> 00:22:24,269
You...

527
00:22:24,270 --> 00:22:26,829
you weren't thrown out
of court, were you?

528
00:22:26,830 --> 00:22:28,070
That would be bad.

529
00:22:28,550 --> 00:22:31,219
You'd be done in Qingcheng Court.

530
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:32,500
Knock it off,

531
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:34,419
don't jinx me.

532
00:22:34,420 --> 00:22:35,870
It's not that dramatic.

533
00:22:36,310 --> 00:22:38,020
Then what happened?

534
00:22:38,350 --> 00:22:40,219
A family of five,

535
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:41,699
parents and three kids,

536
00:22:41,700 --> 00:22:43,789
and just like that,
the divorce is about to be granted.

537
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:47,459
If the judge rules like that,
wouldn't that mean you win the case?

538
00:22:47,460 --> 00:22:48,749
That woman just wanted to use divorce

539
00:22:48,750 --> 00:22:50,069
to scare the man.

540
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:50,829
And the man too,

541
00:22:50,830 --> 00:22:52,139
he just wanted to smooth things over

542
00:22:52,140 --> 00:22:53,219
and get by.

543
00:22:53,220 --> 00:22:55,150
Who knew it would escalate so fast.

544
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:56,829
This is infuriating.

545
00:22:56,830 --> 00:22:57,939
Machine Shen.

546
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,150
What?

547
00:22:59,270 --> 00:23:00,419
Who?

548
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:02,300
I gave that judge a nickname.

549
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:03,749
His name is Shen Xiezhi.

550
00:23:03,750 --> 00:23:06,869
Xiezhi, as the great and upright
mythical beast of justice

551
00:23:06,870 --> 00:23:08,829
that can tell right from wrong.

552
00:23:08,830 --> 00:23:10,910
Shen Xiezhi?

553
00:23:12,110 --> 00:23:14,020
How did he end up
at the grassroots level?

554
00:23:14,380 --> 00:23:16,029
And in family court, no less.

555
00:23:16,030 --> 00:23:17,150
Wait,

556
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:18,589
you know him?

557
00:23:18,590 --> 00:23:19,699
Of course I do.

558
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,659
He is the famous

559
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:23,080
second generation case closing machine

560
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:24,520
from the First Intermediate Court's
criminal division.

561
00:23:24,520 --> 00:23:25,700
Who was the first generation?

562
00:23:26,870 --> 00:23:28,899
I think his surname was Lian.

563
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:30,109
Lian Yongjiu, maybe?

564
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:32,390
I think so. I do not remember clearly.

565
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:34,870
He had already left
before I went to the appraisal center.

566
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,740
But this Machine Shen,

567
00:23:37,270 --> 00:23:39,219
ever since he got transferred
to the intermediate court,

568
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:41,630
he has ranked first in case
closure rate every single year.

569
00:23:41,870 --> 00:23:45,190
Let alone catching up to him,

570
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,350
the second place is nowhere near him.

571
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:53,619
Defendant, do you admit that you did not pay
the plaintiff living expenses on time?

572
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:54,870
I admit it.

573
00:23:55,110 --> 00:23:56,500
(Panel Judge)
Then can you change?

574
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:58,070
Change?

575
00:23:59,070 --> 00:23:59,939
No, I will not.

576
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:01,540
Defendant, watch your attitude.

577
00:24:01,660 --> 00:24:03,979
She takes care of your meals
and clothes every day.

578
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:06,309
And you still think you are justified
in refusing to pay living expenses?

579
00:24:06,310 --> 00:24:08,020
Everything you said is right.

580
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:11,899
Madam, the gentleman knows he was wrong.

581
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,789
Since the two of you
are willing to live together,

582
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:15,379
there must still
be feelings between you.

583
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:17,509
Can you give him another chance?

584
00:24:17,510 --> 00:24:18,590
No.

585
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:20,749
He is stingy to the core.

586
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:21,789
Extremely stingy.

587
00:24:21,790 --> 00:24:23,020
He will never change.

588
00:24:23,220 --> 00:24:25,829
If you are husband and wife,
what is there that cannot be discussed together?

589
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:27,219
He is just trying to live frugally.

590
00:24:27,220 --> 00:24:29,740
It is not that he refuses
to give you money.

591
00:24:30,140 --> 00:24:31,459
As the saying goes,

592
00:24:31,460 --> 00:24:33,939
if a couple is exactly the same,
they will not last till dawn.

593
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:35,619
When husband and wife are too alike,

594
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:38,029
both stubborn and unwilling to give way,

595
00:24:38,030 --> 00:24:40,309
conflicts are more likely to happen.

596
00:24:40,310 --> 00:24:42,309
To live together, you need to
be more tolerant of each other.

597
00:24:42,310 --> 00:24:43,349
Talk through the big things,

598
00:24:43,350 --> 00:24:45,459
and be more understanding
about the small ones.

599
00:24:45,460 --> 00:24:47,379
You cannot blame everything on me.

600
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:49,899
Judge, stop trying to persuade me.

601
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:51,390
This divorce is happening today

602
00:24:51,620 --> 00:24:54,589
whether it has to happen or not.

603
00:24:54,590 --> 00:24:56,179
If you refuse to grant it,

604
00:24:56,180 --> 00:24:58,940
I will stay here
in the courthouse and never leave.

605
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:01,390
Madam, please do not get worked up.

606
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:04,700
Miss,

607
00:25:04,940 --> 00:25:07,350
how am I supposed to explain this?

608
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:08,509
The truth is,

609
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:10,500
this husband of mine cannot be trusted.

610
00:25:10,660 --> 00:25:12,430
He is not just stingy.

611
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:15,979
He gave all his money
to the child from his first marriage.

612
00:25:15,980 --> 00:25:18,700
He still has feelings for his ex wife.

613
00:25:23,030 --> 00:25:25,630
Madam, you are overthinking it.

614
00:25:25,700 --> 00:25:27,419
He is already seventy two this year.

615
00:25:27,420 --> 00:25:29,349
He is long past that stage in life.

616
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:31,549
It has been so many years
since he divorced his ex wife.

617
00:25:31,550 --> 00:25:33,320
There has not been
any feelings left for a long time.

618
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,459
Why are you still jealous
over something so old?

619
00:25:35,460 --> 00:25:37,029
You do not know.

620
00:25:37,030 --> 00:25:38,589
He and his ex wife

621
00:25:38,590 --> 00:25:40,700
used to contact each other
in secret all the time.

622
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:42,619
I put up with it.

623
00:25:42,620 --> 00:25:45,509
But now, he has been secretly
transferring all his pension

624
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:47,269
to that mother and child behind my back.

625
00:25:47,270 --> 00:25:49,260
If there were no feelings involved,

626
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,260
who would believe it?

627
00:25:51,420 --> 00:25:53,830
They have been
moving assets behind my back.

628
00:25:53,940 --> 00:25:56,070
He did not leave me
even a shred of consideration.

629
00:25:56,510 --> 00:25:58,109
I really cannot take it anymore.

630
00:25:58,110 --> 00:25:59,910
If this gets out,

631
00:26:00,030 --> 00:26:01,940
I will be utterly humiliated.

632
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:07,349
Jiang Feng is getting married tomorrow.

633
00:26:07,350 --> 00:26:08,840
I am taking you
to the wedding feast, alright?

634
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,749
Staying home sounds just fine too.

635
00:26:10,750 --> 00:26:12,349
That autopsy report last time

636
00:26:12,350 --> 00:26:15,069
was something our department rushed out
overnight for Jiang Feng.

637
00:26:15,070 --> 00:26:16,699
He specifically said

638
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:20,110
this time he is treating everyone
in our office to the wedding feast.

639
00:26:20,830 --> 00:26:22,509
No charge.

640
00:26:22,510 --> 00:26:23,870
That good?

641
00:26:25,110 --> 00:26:26,029
Found it.

642
00:26:26,030 --> 00:26:28,110
Look, there is good news.

643
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:30,899
What good news?

644
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,540
The bride is you?

645
00:26:35,310 --> 00:26:36,710
(You are cordially invited to attend.
Groom Jiang Feng. Bride Lou Yue.)

646
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:38,700
Lou Yue?

647
00:26:38,750 --> 00:26:40,540
Then I have to go.

648
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:46,989
(We are getting married.
Jiang Feng and Lou Yue)

649
00:26:46,990 --> 00:26:48,990
(Happiness)

650
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:55,790
(Jiang Feng and Lou Yue
welcome everyone to our wedding.)

651
00:26:57,270 --> 00:27:00,390
I thought wedding venues
were always lively.

652
00:27:00,460 --> 00:27:01,659
This place is pretty quiet.

653
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:04,220
Yeah. Are these flowers real or fake?

654
00:27:04,350 --> 00:27:06,740
This is my first time attending
a wedding since graduation.

655
00:27:06,830 --> 00:27:08,150
Same here.

656
00:27:16,110 --> 00:27:17,590
It feels so serious.

657
00:27:17,870 --> 00:27:19,509
The groom's coworkers.

658
00:27:19,510 --> 00:27:21,670
Criminal court judges are all like this.

659
00:27:23,460 --> 00:27:26,220
Getting married
is not easy even for a judge.

660
00:27:27,870 --> 00:27:29,070
Thank you.

661
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,430
I will take one too. Thank you.

662
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:35,029
The food is not even out yet.
There are desserts over here.

663
00:27:35,030 --> 00:27:36,830
I have been craving them
for ages. Hurry.

664
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:39,069
You have really got some nerve.

665
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,740
Eat less.

666
00:27:42,270 --> 00:27:43,740
If it is free, I am eating.

667
00:27:43,740 --> 00:27:46,549
When they come around for toasts later,
help introduce me to the bride.

668
00:27:46,550 --> 00:27:47,459
For what?

669
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:48,419
I want to meet her.

670
00:27:48,420 --> 00:27:49,979
If I end up going
to a top tier law firm later

671
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:50,979
and become a lawyer there,

672
00:27:50,980 --> 00:27:53,070
having her on WeChat
in advance would be great.

673
00:27:53,620 --> 00:27:55,659
That is Ronghe Law Firm.

674
00:27:55,660 --> 00:27:58,029
The minimum requirement is a master's
from a top university

675
00:27:58,030 --> 00:27:59,419
So what?

676
00:27:59,420 --> 00:28:01,589
Worst case, I will pretend to be a fan.

677
00:28:01,590 --> 00:28:03,219
I will ask her for an autograph.

678
00:28:03,220 --> 00:28:04,789
I came all the way to her wedding.

679
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:06,700
She has to give me that much, right?

680
00:28:07,110 --> 00:28:08,789
Alright. Leave it to me.

681
00:28:08,790 --> 00:28:11,220
Eat less.
There is more food coming later.

682
00:28:14,380 --> 00:28:15,700
Where are you going?

683
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:20,379
I have something urgent.

684
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:21,309
What?

685
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,350
Wait.

686
00:28:29,380 --> 00:28:30,670
(Where did he go?)

687
00:28:30,980 --> 00:28:32,300
(Strange.)

688
00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:35,260
(Please, heavens.)

689
00:28:35,270 --> 00:28:37,870
(I cannot afford to have my path
shut off at Qingcheng Court.)

690
00:28:37,980 --> 00:28:39,500
(I have to apologize sincerely.)

691
00:28:39,590 --> 00:28:40,910
Please give me a chance.

692
00:28:41,030 --> 00:28:43,910
I am not getting married today.

693
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:48,640
The three of us are sitting
in the perfect arrangement.

694
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:50,020
I am the plaintiff, he is the defendant.

695
00:28:50,270 --> 00:28:51,659
Today I am taking advantage of you,

696
00:28:51,660 --> 00:28:53,460
so judge this fairly for me.

697
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:55,869
I cannot hold court today.

698
00:28:55,870 --> 00:28:56,899
I am off duty.

699
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:58,179
I am here as the best man.

700
00:28:58,180 --> 00:28:59,419
What now?

701
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,979
We have known each other
for over twenty years.

702
00:29:00,980 --> 00:29:02,680
Are you really going
to make me pay court fees too?

703
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,350
You have to rule on this today.

704
00:29:05,460 --> 00:29:06,549
Yue,

705
00:29:06,550 --> 00:29:08,459
the wedding is about to begin.

706
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:09,589
Please stop being upset.

707
00:29:09,590 --> 00:29:10,699
Stop twisting the facts.

708
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:12,309
And you're still lying to me?

709
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:13,980
Keep your voice down.

710
00:29:14,140 --> 00:29:15,509
This isn't a courtroom.

711
00:29:15,510 --> 00:29:16,789
This is between us.

712
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:18,540
Let's talk it through calmly.

713
00:29:19,070 --> 00:29:20,419
The three of us grew up together,

714
00:29:20,420 --> 00:29:22,150
we've known each other
since we were kids, right?

715
00:29:24,750 --> 00:29:26,269
From where I stand,

716
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:27,139
in this situation,

717
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,870
I can't stay impartial.

718
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:30,419
I request to step aside.

719
00:29:30,420 --> 00:29:31,460
Stay right there.

720
00:29:32,350 --> 00:29:33,500
Judge Jiang,

721
00:29:33,590 --> 00:29:34,699
is this your first day knowing

722
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:37,220
there's a recusal rule
between judges and lawyers?

723
00:29:37,870 --> 00:29:39,379
When you moved
to the intermediate court,

724
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:41,459
I already gave up
half business of Tianhai City.

725
00:29:41,460 --> 00:29:43,300
Now you're heading to the high court.

726
00:29:43,420 --> 00:29:44,269
Tell me,

727
00:29:44,270 --> 00:29:45,619
what options do I even have left?

728
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:47,350
Should I just quit being a lawyer?

729
00:29:47,460 --> 00:29:48,939
If they hadn't let it slip today,

730
00:29:48,940 --> 00:29:51,349
how long were you planning
to keep this from me?

731
00:29:51,350 --> 00:29:53,309
That was on me, I didn't call you.

732
00:29:53,310 --> 00:29:54,179
But on WeChat,

733
00:29:54,180 --> 00:29:56,029
didn't I explain everything clearly?

734
00:29:56,030 --> 00:29:57,619
When have you ever messaged me?

735
00:29:57,620 --> 00:29:59,139
Or did I suddenly lose my memory,

736
00:29:59,140 --> 00:30:00,549
and now you're just making things up?

737
00:30:00,550 --> 00:30:02,110
Making things up?

738
00:30:03,220 --> 00:30:04,029
Hold on.

739
00:30:04,030 --> 00:30:05,110
Go ahead, find it.

740
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:11,419
When have I ever sent you anything?

741
00:30:11,420 --> 00:30:12,670
You...

742
00:30:13,460 --> 00:30:15,190
Read it to her.

743
00:30:15,220 --> 00:30:16,590
Here, take it.

744
00:30:16,620 --> 00:30:17,629
Read it.

745
00:30:17,630 --> 00:30:19,390
(Yue, there's something
I want to talk to you about...)

746
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:22,789
Jiang Feng said,

747
00:30:22,790 --> 00:30:23,699
Yue,

748
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:25,869
there's something
I want to talk to you about.

749
00:30:25,870 --> 00:30:27,749
I've been accepted by the high court.

750
00:30:27,750 --> 00:30:29,459
This opportunity doesn't come easy.

751
00:30:29,460 --> 00:30:30,780
Yue said,

752
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:32,509
this is too much.

753
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:34,459
At a time like this,
you're throwing me off balance.

754
00:30:34,460 --> 00:30:36,459
Let's switch to a backup plan.

755
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:38,939
Worst case, I'll move
into international litigation.

756
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:40,789
Jiang Feng said, are you sure, Yue?

757
00:30:40,790 --> 00:30:42,179
I'm really touched.

758
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,459
Yue said, what choice do I have?

759
00:30:43,460 --> 00:30:44,979
At this point, what else can I say?

760
00:30:44,980 --> 00:30:46,780
That's enough.

761
00:30:47,420 --> 00:30:48,869
I never sent those messages.

762
00:30:48,870 --> 00:30:50,110
Judge Jiang,

763
00:30:50,180 --> 00:30:51,899
so now you're fabricating evidence?

764
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:53,219
Fabricating what?

765
00:30:53,220 --> 00:30:54,459
You sent these to me.

766
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:55,749
You've got to be kidding.

767
00:30:55,750 --> 00:30:57,899
When did I ever send
something like that?

768
00:30:57,900 --> 00:30:59,830
It was me.

769
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:06,630
Yue,

770
00:31:06,700 --> 00:31:07,740
that day,

771
00:31:07,980 --> 00:31:09,899
when you were trying
on your wedding dress,

772
00:31:09,900 --> 00:31:12,500
I used your phone to reply.

773
00:31:13,070 --> 00:31:15,740
Then I deleted the messages.

774
00:31:16,940 --> 00:31:18,219
I... I know, Yue,

775
00:31:18,220 --> 00:31:20,459
it hasn't been easy
for you two to come this far.

776
00:31:20,460 --> 00:31:22,349
You can't fall apart right
at the finish line.

777
00:31:22,350 --> 00:31:23,349
Mom!

778
00:31:23,350 --> 00:31:24,350
I...

779
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:26,139
Is this supposed to help me?

780
00:31:26,140 --> 00:31:28,260
I'm sorry.

781
00:31:30,350 --> 00:31:31,349
Mom meant well.

782
00:31:31,350 --> 00:31:32,350
Alright.

783
00:31:34,350 --> 00:31:35,700
Now everything's clear.

784
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,740
This is our fault.

785
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:38,749
I apologize to you.

786
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:39,699
It's fine, we're family.

787
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:41,940
This wedding is canceled.

788
00:31:42,030 --> 00:31:43,029
Leave.

789
00:31:43,030 --> 00:31:45,029
- Get out, all of you!
- What? No, that's not...

790
00:31:45,030 --> 00:31:46,899
My head is a mess right now.

791
00:31:46,900 --> 00:31:49,419
I don't want to talk to any of you.

792
00:31:49,420 --> 00:31:52,190
Not one of you thought about how I feel.

793
00:31:52,980 --> 00:31:54,549
Yue.

794
00:31:54,550 --> 00:31:57,179
It's all my fault.

795
00:31:57,180 --> 00:31:58,179
I'm sorry.

796
00:31:58,180 --> 00:32:00,260
I'm sorry.

797
00:32:01,510 --> 00:32:02,740
Where are you going?

798
00:32:03,790 --> 00:32:05,349
Go talk to her,

799
00:32:05,350 --> 00:32:09,109
say something nice, help her calm down.
This is something you need to handle yourself.

800
00:32:09,110 --> 00:32:10,630
On my own, I...

801
00:32:11,270 --> 00:32:12,460
Not...

802
00:32:15,980 --> 00:32:16,789
Yue.

803
00:32:16,790 --> 00:32:17,379
Go away.

804
00:32:17,380 --> 00:32:18,309
I was wrong, okay?

805
00:32:18,310 --> 00:32:19,980
Please don't be like this.

806
00:32:23,310 --> 00:32:24,830
Why are you here?

807
00:32:27,550 --> 00:32:29,300
Sorry...

808
00:32:29,620 --> 00:32:31,659
I thought this was the restroom.

809
00:32:31,660 --> 00:32:32,940
I came to the wrong place.

810
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:35,070
Are you following me again?

811
00:32:36,700 --> 00:32:38,830
What do you mean following you?

812
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:40,789
I'm here for the wedding too.

813
00:32:40,790 --> 00:32:42,300
You two know each other, right?

814
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:43,789
Take her outside and talk.

815
00:32:43,790 --> 00:32:45,269
We'll deal with our own situation.

816
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:46,659
I didn't come here for him.

817
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:47,870
Ms. Lou,

818
00:32:47,940 --> 00:32:49,139
I'm not here because of him.

819
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:50,870
I'm actually here to talk to you.

820
00:32:51,980 --> 00:32:54,910
I know I'm not really
in a position to speak today.

821
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:57,549
I'm a family court lawyer.

822
00:32:57,550 --> 00:32:58,899
I've handled many cases like this.

823
00:32:58,900 --> 00:33:01,109
A lot of people regret divorce

824
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:03,590
even right after leaving the courthouse.

825
00:33:03,700 --> 00:33:05,459
Love isn't something to take lightly.

826
00:33:05,460 --> 00:33:06,659
And from what I can tell,

827
00:33:06,660 --> 00:33:08,549
you've known each other for years.

828
00:33:08,550 --> 00:33:09,899
After all that time together,

829
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:11,869
ending it like this
would be such a shame.

830
00:33:11,870 --> 00:33:15,110
This is someone else's private matter.
What does it have to do with you? Get out.

831
00:33:15,310 --> 00:33:16,589
Xiezhi,

832
00:33:16,590 --> 00:33:18,070
let her speak.

833
00:33:18,460 --> 00:33:20,780
Help me talk some sense into her.

834
00:33:21,220 --> 00:33:22,460
Come on.

835
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:26,780
Let her finish.

836
00:33:28,750 --> 00:33:29,980
Ms. Lou,

837
00:33:30,220 --> 00:33:31,430
I know

838
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:34,150
you're an outstanding lawyer,

839
00:33:34,350 --> 00:33:36,899
and I'm just a family court lawyer,

840
00:33:36,900 --> 00:33:38,459
but I've handled plenty

841
00:33:38,460 --> 00:33:39,659
of cases like this.

842
00:33:39,660 --> 00:33:41,590
I once had a couple as clients...

843
00:33:49,870 --> 00:33:52,510
(Where are you?)

844
00:33:55,030 --> 00:33:57,940
Life is finite, but love is not.

845
00:33:58,030 --> 00:34:01,390
The road is long, and so is affection.

846
00:34:01,790 --> 00:34:03,939
Marriage is about giving.

847
00:34:03,940 --> 00:34:05,459
The sweeter the love,

848
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:06,899
the more understanding a marriage needs.

849
00:34:06,900 --> 00:34:08,220
Right, Auntie?

850
00:34:08,460 --> 00:34:09,860
Exactly.

851
00:34:09,940 --> 00:34:13,379
Marriage is all about give

852
00:34:13,380 --> 00:34:14,820
and take.

853
00:34:14,870 --> 00:34:16,629
She put it so well.

854
00:34:16,630 --> 00:34:18,990
No wonder she's a family court lawyer.

855
00:34:19,020 --> 00:34:20,420
You're too kind.

856
00:34:24,420 --> 00:34:26,349
The opening performances
are already over.

857
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:28,059
The host must be rushing things along.

858
00:34:28,060 --> 00:34:29,019
You two,

859
00:34:29,020 --> 00:34:30,579
get out there now.

860
00:34:30,580 --> 00:34:31,629
Yes, the wedding.

861
00:34:31,630 --> 00:34:32,869
Come on, let's go.

862
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:34,190
Get up.

863
00:34:39,270 --> 00:34:40,379
Xiezhi,

864
00:34:40,380 --> 00:34:42,670
say something.

865
00:34:43,870 --> 00:34:45,740
Go on, say something.

866
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:48,150
Say it.

867
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:51,309
Say a few words.

868
00:34:51,310 --> 00:34:52,420
Come on.

869
00:34:54,870 --> 00:34:56,070
Let me

870
00:34:56,750 --> 00:34:59,070
ask you both three questions

871
00:34:59,310 --> 00:35:01,019
to help you sort this out,

872
00:35:01,020 --> 00:35:03,309
so you can figure out
what you really want

873
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:05,419
and decide what to do next.

874
00:35:05,420 --> 00:35:06,630
Fine.

875
00:35:09,460 --> 00:35:10,820
First question.

876
00:35:12,380 --> 00:35:14,019
Can you accept a long distance marriage?

877
00:35:14,020 --> 00:35:15,059
No.

878
00:35:15,060 --> 00:35:16,099
A husband

879
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:17,379
is a husband only within arm's reach.

880
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:18,669
Once he's far away,

881
00:35:18,670 --> 00:35:20,340
he might as well be an ex.

882
00:35:20,580 --> 00:35:22,700
It's not sustainable.

883
00:35:23,670 --> 00:35:24,629
Second question.

884
00:35:24,630 --> 00:35:26,979
If either of you
makes a sacrifice today,

885
00:35:26,980 --> 00:35:27,869
will it become a reason

886
00:35:27,870 --> 00:35:30,300
to guilt the other later?

887
00:35:30,500 --> 00:35:32,189
I would never guilt you.

888
00:35:32,190 --> 00:35:33,780
And I'm not quitting my job.

889
00:35:34,710 --> 00:35:35,789
Alright.

890
00:35:35,790 --> 00:35:37,030
Third question.

891
00:35:37,830 --> 00:35:39,030
Jiang Feng,

892
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:41,740
do you see turning down
this promotion as a sacrifice?

893
00:35:49,190 --> 00:35:51,110
I won't accept your sacrifice.

894
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:54,590
Jiang Feng,

895
00:35:55,270 --> 00:35:56,780
face yourself,

896
00:35:57,420 --> 00:35:59,110
and face reality.

897
00:36:01,630 --> 00:36:03,260
Better a short pain than a long one.

898
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:07,189
That's not how it is.

899
00:36:07,190 --> 00:36:08,780
That's not how it is.

900
00:36:08,830 --> 00:36:10,709
How did it come to this?

901
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:11,869
We can talk this through.

902
00:36:11,870 --> 00:36:14,269
- Talk it through.
- Mom, get up, please.

903
00:36:14,270 --> 00:36:16,700
We can work this out.

904
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:19,869
I shouldn't have let you speak.

905
00:36:19,870 --> 00:36:22,220
Just go, get out.

906
00:36:23,830 --> 00:36:25,470
You two,

907
00:36:25,540 --> 00:36:27,149
go talk it over properly.

908
00:36:27,150 --> 00:36:28,499
Yes, think it through carefully.

909
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:29,539
Really think about it.

910
00:36:29,540 --> 00:36:30,629
Yue.

911
00:36:30,630 --> 00:36:31,309
What are you doing?

912
00:36:31,310 --> 00:36:32,780
Yue.

913
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:34,869
What are you doing?

914
00:36:34,870 --> 00:36:36,190
Jiang Feng.

915
00:36:42,830 --> 00:36:44,190
What are you doing?

916
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:47,700
They're your friends too.

917
00:36:47,710 --> 00:36:49,019
They don't even want a divorce.

918
00:36:49,020 --> 00:36:49,939
What are you doing?

919
00:36:49,940 --> 00:36:51,349
How can you break them up like this?

920
00:36:51,350 --> 00:36:52,379
Do you know what it means

921
00:36:52,380 --> 00:36:54,990
to cut your losses in time?

922
00:36:55,270 --> 00:36:56,059
An outstanding judge

923
00:36:56,060 --> 00:36:57,860
and an outstanding lawyer together

924
00:36:57,980 --> 00:36:59,669
could very well end in tragedy.

925
00:36:59,670 --> 00:37:02,419
Should they wait until they have children
before talking about breaking up?

926
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:04,700
My client's situation is different.

927
00:37:05,020 --> 00:37:05,789
Right?

928
00:37:05,790 --> 00:37:08,229
No one says a working person
and a homemaker can't be together.

929
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:09,789
A working person?

930
00:37:09,790 --> 00:37:12,459
His wife had three children for him
and is left with lasting health issues.

931
00:37:12,460 --> 00:37:14,150
And he's out there fooling around.

932
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:15,269
He's no better than an animal.

933
00:37:15,270 --> 00:37:16,539
Not everyone has the courage

934
00:37:16,540 --> 00:37:18,040
to be as clear cut as you.

935
00:37:18,040 --> 00:37:19,800
Once married,
there's a bond that's hard to break.

936
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,749
I'll make sure the innocent party

937
00:37:21,750 --> 00:37:24,150
gets the most favorable share
in the property division.

938
00:37:24,670 --> 00:37:25,900
Judge Shen,

939
00:37:25,980 --> 00:37:27,670
why won't you believe me?

940
00:37:27,710 --> 00:37:30,059
My client truly doesn't
want to separate.

941
00:37:30,060 --> 00:37:32,550
With what you've done,
why should I believe you?

942
00:37:34,190 --> 00:37:35,379
Let me say it again.

943
00:37:35,380 --> 00:37:37,149
Either she withdraws the case herself,

944
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:39,459
or your client comes to me in person.

945
00:37:39,460 --> 00:37:41,190
There's no third option.

946
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:42,529
You...

947
00:37:42,530 --> 00:37:44,260
Stop following me.

948
00:37:48,230 --> 00:37:49,499
Why don't you go be a terminator?

949
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,550
What are you even doing in family court?

950
00:38:01,870 --> 00:38:02,990
Slippers.

951
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:07,899
Just crash at my place tonight.

952
00:38:07,900 --> 00:38:09,820
I'd be grateful if you let me stay.

953
00:38:10,060 --> 00:38:11,300
You know what?

954
00:38:12,980 --> 00:38:15,309
I can't even stay at home anymore.

955
00:38:15,310 --> 00:38:17,149
Right now it's wife first, son second.

956
00:38:17,150 --> 00:38:19,340
If the wife's gone, the son's out too.

957
00:38:20,230 --> 00:38:22,190
How is this my fault?

958
00:38:29,580 --> 00:38:30,670
Then whose fault is it?

959
00:38:31,980 --> 00:38:34,300
I really don't understand
what you're thinking.

960
00:38:34,630 --> 00:38:36,939
- You dragged your feet before, fine,
- Me...

961
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:41,379
but the transfer order is already out,
and you still didn't tell Lou Yue in person.

962
00:38:41,380 --> 00:38:43,189
She's that busy,
and you just sent a message.

963
00:38:43,190 --> 00:38:44,640
You probably hoped
she wouldn't even see it.

964
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,059
Don't worry about how I handled it.

965
00:38:46,060 --> 00:38:47,829
She replied in the end, didn't she?

966
00:38:47,830 --> 00:38:48,629
Look at you.

967
00:38:48,630 --> 00:38:50,499
You're still refusing to face reality.

968
00:38:50,500 --> 00:38:51,979
You just couldn't face Lou Yue,

969
00:38:51,980 --> 00:38:53,700
didn't dare tell her to her face.

970
00:38:53,710 --> 00:38:54,789
You timed that message

971
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:56,579
so her mother would see it, didn't you?

972
00:38:56,580 --> 00:38:58,189
No matter what,

973
00:38:58,190 --> 00:38:59,340
you've got to help me.

974
00:38:59,420 --> 00:39:00,709
I already did.

975
00:39:00,710 --> 00:39:02,669
I'm letting you stay
at my place tonight.

976
00:39:02,670 --> 00:39:04,670
Whose side are you on?

977
00:39:04,940 --> 00:39:06,419
On my wedding night,

978
00:39:06,420 --> 00:39:07,459
my bride's gone,

979
00:39:07,460 --> 00:39:08,579
my family's torn apart,

980
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:10,019
and I can't even go home.

981
00:39:10,020 --> 00:39:11,979
What kind of judge
writes a fate like this?

982
00:39:11,980 --> 00:39:13,110
Where's the justice?

983
00:39:13,190 --> 00:39:14,579
Your case hasn't reached final judgment.

984
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:15,829
You still have the right to appeal.

985
00:39:15,830 --> 00:39:17,349
Face reality

986
00:39:17,350 --> 00:39:18,820
and try to get a suspended sentence.

987
00:39:19,060 --> 00:39:20,190
Brother,

988
00:39:20,310 --> 00:39:23,869
I came here for comfort. If you can't say
anything helpful, just stay quiet.

989
00:39:23,870 --> 00:39:26,379
Comfort isn't going to fix anything.

990
00:39:26,380 --> 00:39:27,709
What you need now

991
00:39:27,710 --> 00:39:31,340
is to reflect,
make changes, and start over.

992
00:39:45,790 --> 00:39:47,950
Wake up, we're almost there.

993
00:40:01,750 --> 00:40:03,950
It's fine. Your makeup has been smudged.

994
00:40:04,060 --> 00:40:06,019
How are you this sleepy?

995
00:40:06,020 --> 00:40:08,030
Why didn't you wake me earlier?

996
00:40:08,380 --> 00:40:09,979
I tried several times.

997
00:40:09,980 --> 00:40:11,740
You were sleeping like a log.

998
00:40:12,150 --> 00:40:13,900
Are you pregnant?

999
00:40:14,380 --> 00:40:15,709
Pregnant with what?

1000
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:17,149
We're following the plan.

1001
00:40:17,150 --> 00:40:18,740
It's not time yet.

1002
00:40:19,060 --> 00:40:22,190
Preparing for pregnancy
is like preparing for an exam.

1003
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:24,190
What do you mean?

1004
00:40:25,190 --> 00:40:26,340
What's wrong?

1005
00:40:28,270 --> 00:40:30,260
This is serious.

1006
00:40:30,270 --> 00:40:32,019
Diet, routine, nutrition, exercise,

1007
00:40:32,020 --> 00:40:33,149
none of it can be taken lightly.

1008
00:40:33,150 --> 00:40:34,700
I need focus on driving.

1009
00:40:35,310 --> 00:40:37,059
I just want to get
my body in the best shape

1010
00:40:37,060 --> 00:40:39,349
so the baby
has the healthiest start possible.

1011
00:40:39,350 --> 00:40:41,099
From day one,
we're aiming ahead of the curve.

1012
00:40:41,100 --> 00:40:42,379
Do you understand?

1013
00:40:42,380 --> 00:40:44,820
But timing matters too.

1014
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:45,749
Honey,

1015
00:40:45,750 --> 00:40:47,229
I get it,

1016
00:40:47,230 --> 00:40:49,820
but the perfect timing
doesn't wait for you.

1017
00:40:52,190 --> 00:40:53,510
Enough.

1018
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:55,749
We'll stick to the plan step by step.

1019
00:40:55,750 --> 00:40:57,459
We can't skip anything.

1020
00:40:57,460 --> 00:40:59,070
When the time is right,

1021
00:40:59,790 --> 00:41:01,380
it will happen naturally.

1022
00:41:02,540 --> 00:41:03,709
You should've said that earlier.

1023
00:41:03,710 --> 00:41:05,470
Now I feel more at ease.

1024
00:41:07,940 --> 00:41:09,420
I'll focus on driving.

1025
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:15,750
(Qingcheng No.5 Primary School)

1026
00:41:16,380 --> 00:41:17,229
Fei,

1027
00:41:17,230 --> 00:41:18,630
are you wearing your watch?

1028
00:41:19,020 --> 00:41:20,300
Is it charged?

1029
00:41:23,580 --> 00:41:24,950
What about the spray?

1030
00:41:29,870 --> 00:41:31,149
How many times have I told you

1031
00:41:31,150 --> 00:41:32,499
to bring these things?

1032
00:41:32,500 --> 00:41:34,190
Good thing I brought backups.

1033
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:36,899
From now on,

1034
00:41:36,900 --> 00:41:38,629
you must bring these to school.

1035
00:41:38,630 --> 00:41:39,349
Got it?

1036
00:41:39,350 --> 00:41:41,860
And when you leave school,
make sure you still have them.

1037
00:41:53,350 --> 00:41:54,470
Honey,

1038
00:41:54,830 --> 00:41:56,579
I'm heading to the airport later.

1039
00:41:56,580 --> 00:41:58,749
Take care of yourself while I'm away.

1040
00:41:58,750 --> 00:41:59,539
Love you.

1041
00:41:59,540 --> 00:42:00,670
Love you.

1042
00:42:06,270 --> 00:42:07,059
Morning.

1043
00:42:07,060 --> 00:42:08,190
Morning.

1044
00:42:09,190 --> 00:42:10,059
Morning, Le.

1045
00:42:10,060 --> 00:42:10,749
Morning.

1046
00:42:10,750 --> 00:42:12,059
Have you eaten?

1047
00:42:12,060 --> 00:42:13,300
We have.

1048
00:42:20,630 --> 00:42:21,789
Morning, Le.

1049
00:42:21,790 --> 00:42:22,820
Morning.

1050
00:42:24,100 --> 00:42:26,700
I brought today's case files for you.

1051
00:42:27,540 --> 00:42:28,820
That's quite a lot.

1052
00:42:34,270 --> 00:42:35,420
What are you doing?

1053
00:42:36,100 --> 00:42:39,030
Taking so many pills
isn't good for your liver.

1054
00:42:39,190 --> 00:42:42,220
These are vitamins
for preparing for pregnancy.

1055
00:42:42,310 --> 00:42:44,539
You've been trying
for so long with no results,

1056
00:42:44,540 --> 00:42:46,379
I thought you'd changed your mind.

1057
00:42:46,380 --> 00:42:49,590
Well, before this,
Xiao Bing had to drink at a work event.

1058
00:42:50,060 --> 00:42:52,990
The doctor said no alcohol
for at least half a year when trying.

1059
00:42:53,150 --> 00:42:54,669
Then I caught the flu,

1060
00:42:54,670 --> 00:42:56,419
so we had to wait again.

1061
00:42:56,420 --> 00:42:58,220
That set us back
another couple of months.

1062
00:42:59,420 --> 00:43:00,539
You're not married yet.

1063
00:43:00,540 --> 00:43:02,860
There's a lot to pay attention to
when preparing for pregnancy.

1064
00:43:14,620 --> 00:43:18,080
♪All the little things
between you and me♪

1065
00:43:18,080 --> 00:43:20,760
♪Woven into our lives♪

1066
00:43:21,610 --> 00:43:23,590
♪The building blocks of life♪

1067
00:43:23,590 --> 00:43:25,290
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1068
00:43:25,290 --> 00:43:27,450
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1069
00:43:27,770 --> 00:43:30,450
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1070
00:43:31,330 --> 00:43:35,150
♪Some questions weigh like mountains♪

1071
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,380
♪How do we piece life back together?♪

1072
00:43:40,940 --> 00:43:45,130
♪So hate can fade
and love feels new again♪

1073
00:43:45,130 --> 00:43:48,200
♪Reclaim the barren parts of life♪

1074
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:54,570
♪Walking this road
together, still hoping♪

1075
00:43:55,360 --> 00:44:00,420
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

1076
00:44:00,720 --> 00:44:04,690
♪Blowing away all the pain♪

1077
00:44:04,920 --> 00:44:09,900
♪Let me be the balance
that holds the weight♪

1078
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
♪Where fairness stands♪

1079
00:44:15,350 --> 00:44:17,590
♪Within every heart♪

1080
00:44:17,590 --> 00:44:20,240
♪So many voices calling♪

1081
00:44:20,500 --> 00:44:24,790
♪Struggling, lost,
waiting for an answer♪

1082
00:44:24,790 --> 00:44:27,140
♪Light up the lamps♪

1083
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,810
♪To answer those voices♪

1084
00:44:30,120 --> 00:44:32,240
♪You deserve to be happy♪

1085
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:34,990
♪Loud and clear♪

1086
00:44:34,990 --> 00:44:37,310
♪All the little things♪

1087
00:44:37,310 --> 00:44:40,010
♪Woven into our lives♪

1088
00:44:40,830 --> 00:44:42,880
♪The building blocks of life♪

1089
00:44:42,880 --> 00:44:44,590
♪Shape the sky above us♪

1090
00:44:44,590 --> 00:44:47,040
♪Are you doing alright?♪

1091
00:44:47,040 --> 00:44:49,150
♪What are you struggling for?♪

1092
00:44:49,400 --> 00:44:51,530
♪Some questions♪

1093
00:44:52,100 --> 00:44:54,800
♪Weigh like mountains♪

1094
00:44:57,690 --> 00:45:02,840
♪Let me be the wind at dawn♪

